# LendeX вҖ” Peer-to-Peer Rental Marketplace
## Initial Project Draft

---

## 1. Project Idea

**LendeX** is a full-stack, peer-to-peer rental marketplace that connects people who own high-value assets (cameras, vehicles, gaming gear, professional tools, outdoor equipment) with people who need them temporarily. Unlike traditional e-commerce where items are sold, LendeX is built entirely around **short-term rentals with verified security deposits**, enabling owners to monetize idle assets while renters access premium gear without the upfront ownership cost.

The platform is inspired by the density, professionalism, and trustworthiness of industry leaders like **Amazon**, **Flipkart**, and **Airbnb**, but specialized for the rental economy across physical goods.

---

## 2. Objectives

| # | Objective | Priority |
|---|-----------|----------|
| 1 | Provide a trusted, frictionless platform for renters to discover and book premium equipment | High |
| 2 | Enable verified merchants to list, manage, and monetize their assets | High |
| 3 | Implement secure payment collection including refundable security deposits | High |
| 4 | Deliver a premium, Amazon-level UI with category navigation, search, and filtering | High |
| 5 | Support real-time messaging between renters and owners | Medium |
| 6 | Provide an admin dashboard for monitoring listings, disputes, and users | Medium |
| 7 | Enforce identity verification and product condition auditing | Medium |

---

## 3. Target Users

- **Renters**: Students, creators, professionals, and hobbyists who need premium gear for short durations (1вҖ“30 days)
- **Merchants / Owners**: Individuals or small businesses who own high-value equipment and want to earn passive income from it
- **Admins**: Platform operators managing disputes, verifying users, and monitoring activity

---

## 4. Proposed Approach

### 4.1 Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| **Frontend** | HTML5 + CSS3 (Custom Design System) + Vanilla JS (ES Modules) |
| **Backend** | Node.js + Express.js (REST API) |
| **Database** | Firebase Firestore (NoSQL, real-time capable) |
| **Auth** | Firebase Authentication (Email/Password + Google OAuth) |
| **Payments** | Razorpay (order creation + server-side verification) |
| **File Storage** | Firebase Storage (product images) |
| **Hosting** | Express static serving (localhost:5000); deployable to Railway/Render |

